katexR Example

February 3, 2015

This is an R Markdown document. Lets see how we might use it with the katexR htmlwidget.

OMG, Look at My KaTeX

library(katexR)
library(htmltools)

as.tags(katexR( "\\frac{1}{n} \\sum_{i=i}^{n} x_{i}", tag="p", style = "font-size:300%;" ))

# without the as.tags() enclosure
katexR( "\\frac{1}{n} \\sum_{i=i}^{n} x_{i}", tag="span", style = "font-size:300%;" )

KaTeX the hard way

Now, since we get the KaTeX dependencies with katexR, we can also use them bare. If you dont anticipate already having a katexR() call in the document, then you can just do an empty katexR() to bring in the dependencies.

<h5 style="text-align:center;" ><span id = "katex-from-scratch"></span> with `katexR`</h5>
<script>
katex.render('\KaTeX',document.getElementById('katex-from-scratch'))
</script>
with katexR

Inline KaTeX

Now, lets go back to one rendered by our katexR function like this with some inline R code to see how we get it in a paragraph. In mean would look something like this . Unfortunately, you might notice, that we have to enclose it in as.tags(...) to make it work, but hey it does work.
